Eventually I ran into some nice people who helped, and we had a Mage, Ranger, 2 Druids, and a Shaman.  We nailed him twice in just over an hour, by clearing everything around the Undertow/Seahorse Caves area.  Both Druids happy :)<br>
<br>
Ulump we did with 7 people.  2 Rangers, Warrior, Cleric, Shaman, Monk and Druid.  All 57+ .  He aggroes from a long way off, and caught us by surprise.  We recovered and kicked his butt.  Not too tough.  <br>
<br>
Faydedar:  22 people, all high level.  We owned him completely.  I think 2 high lvl groups can do it.  Make sure your resists are high.<br>
<br>
The Brownie was cake.  Myself and a 59 Ranger tore him up.<br>
He's up regularly anyway, just zone in and track occasionally.<br>
<br>
With all the grouped fights, you should have a strong tank.  He needs to hold aggro completely.  If the healer looks after him, you win.  Simple as that.<br>
<br>
<br>
